Senate Resolution 476
By: Senators Halpern of the 39th, Hickman of the 4th, Dixon of the 45th, Sims of the 12th,
Williams of the 25th and others
ADOPTED SENATE
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Senate Study Committee on Local School System Flexibility Options; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Georgia law permits the State Board of Education to waive compliance with
4 certain provisions of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated to grant flexibility
5 to local school systems and charter schools with the goal of improving student performance;
6 and
7 WHEREAS, local school systems and charter schools are authorized to seek exemptions
8 from state laws and regulations, including but not limited to class size requirements, teacher
9 salary minimums, special education provisions, curriculum standards, and operational
10 guidelines; and
11 WHEREAS, all but two of Georgia's 180 local school systems currently hold class size
12 waivers, potentially impacting student learning environments and teacher workload; and
13 WHEREAS, local school systems utilizing waivers may also modify compensation
14 structures, certification requirements, teacher planning time, and student support services,
