15 raising questions about the long-term effects on educator retention and instructional quality;
16 and
17 WHEREAS, the Georgia State Board of Education recently extended all existing waivers for
18 an additional five years, underscoring the need for a comprehensive review of their
19 implementation, effectiveness, and oversight; and
20 WHEREAS, a thorough study is necessary to assess whether the flexibility provided by
21 waivers has enhanced educational outcomes, improved operational efficiency, and
22 maintained equity and accountability across local school systems.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE:
24 (1) Creation of Senate study committee. There is created the Senate Study Committee
25 on Local School System Flexibility Options.
26 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of six members of the
27 Senate to be appointed as follows:
28 (A) Four members appointed by the President of the Senate; and
29 (B) Two members appointed by the Senate Minority Leader.
30 The President shall designate a member of the committee as chairperson of the
31 committee.
32 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
33 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
34 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
35 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
36 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
37 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
38 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
